  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0b9a\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b9a\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba3\u0bbf \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sajith's team decided to vote against the Emergency Act",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Parliamentary Committee and Executive Committee Meeting of United People's Power and United People's Alliance met today (26.07.2022) and reached the following conclusions.",
        "01). It was unanimously decided to vote against the Emergency Act, which was brought in to suppress the right to freedom of expression, the right to protest and the rights of people to protest against issues they face on a daily basis.",
        "02). It was decided not to collude with an oppressive government that directly and indirectly unleashed state terror without providing real solutions to people's problems.",
        "03). It was decided to support the establishment of a committee system in the Parliament to resolve the day-to-day problems of the people in the parliamentary democratic system."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "Sajith",
          "label": "PERSON"
        },
        {
          "text": "the Emergency Act",
          "label": "LAW"
        }
